Three bars have been closed in Mbitini for operating outside the required time.Speaking on Monday during Jamhuri Day celebrations, assistant county commissioner Njaga Njagi said the licences of the bars in Kyumbuni sublocation have been revoked for operating for 24 hours.He addressed wananchi at Mungyani Market. Njagi threatened to close all bars in the division found selling liquor to children.On land sale, Njagi told residents to sell their land with family consent to avoid wrangles.Makueni MP Daniel Maanzo, who also addressed the gathering, cautioned the youth against being misused by political leaders, who preach hatred and insults during campaign rallies.